What parameters to geom_jitter() control the amount of jittering? width and height

3

Compare and contrast geom_jitter() with geom_count(). From Description: Count: Counts the number of observations at each location, then maps the count to point area. Jitter: Adds a small amount of random variation to the location of each point.

Compare and contrast Both are useful when you have discrete data and overplotting. Jitter randomly moved the points to stop overlapping - count counts the points ar a given coordinate and reflects that in the size of the point. So for large datasets of discrete data where the point is exact it is useful - if the points are close but not exact Jitter is more useful for visualization.

?geom_count()
?mpg
